export const MINDSTATE_FRAMEWORK_OVERVIEW = "Mindstate Marketing Framework (Will Leach)\n\nAPPROACH: How people make decisions\n- Cautious (Loss-Avoidance): Focus on avoiding mistakes, minimizing risk, preventing loss\n- Optimistic (Gain-Seeking): Focus on gaining benefits, pursuing opportunities, maximizing upside\n\nMOTIVATION: 8 Universal Human Motivations\n1. Achievement - Desire for success, accomplishment, overcoming obstacles\n2. Autonomy - Desire for freedom, independence, self-determination  \n3. Belonging - Desire for acceptance, connection, community\n4. Competence - Desire for mastery, skill development, personal growth\n5. Empowerment - Desire for control, agency, being equipped\n6. Engagement - Desire for curiosity, stimulation, novelty\n7. Esteem - Desire for status, respect, recognition\n8. Nurturance - Desire to care for others, help, provide support\n9. Security - Desire for safety, stability, predictability\n\nTHE 3-STEP ACTIVATION PROCESS:\nStep 1 - IDENTIFY: Determine customer's dominant mindstate (motivation + approach combination)\nStep 2 - PRIME: Activate the specific motivation through messaging and emotional cues\nStep 3 - FRAME: Present brand/product in a way that matches their psychological approach\n\nKEY PRINCIPLES FOR AI AD GENERATION:\n- Use cognitive triggers (heuristics) to make decisions feel intuitive\n- Lead with visuals that evoke desired emotional states\n- Reinforce with copy that validates the emotional connection\n- Ensure consistency: every touchpoint reflects the same psychological position\n";

